    (7,"easy","Law Commission reports ఎవరికి submit? / To whom are Law Commission reports submitted?",
     "Parliament","Ministry of Law and Justice","President","CJI","b",
     "Law Commission reports are submitted to the Ministry of Law and Justice. / LCI reports to: Ministry of Law and Justice."),
    (7,"hard","Post-independence Law Commissions ఎంత? / How many post-independence Law Commissions?",
     "10","15","22","30","c",
     "22 Law Commissions in post-independence India (as of latest count). / Post-independence: 22 Law Commissions."),
    (7,"medium","లా కమిషన్ నివేదికలు binding గా ఉంటాయా? / Are Law Commission reports binding?",
     "Yes — binding on courts","No — advisory only; government has discretion to accept/reject","Binding on all ministries","Binding on Parliament","b",
     "Law Commission reports: advisory only, NOT binding. Government has discretion. / LCI reports: advisory, not binding."),
